ttps://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/3541", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/3541", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/3541.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/3541.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Generate random uniform floats in the range [0, 1) by generating random<br>\nuniform uint32 in the range [0, 2^24-1] and dividing by 2^24. This<br>\nensures that the largest value is representable as a float32 less than<br>\none.</p>\n<p>This also changes the uniform double generation to use more bits of<br>\nrandomness.</p>", "body_text": "Generate random uniform floats in the range [0, 1) by generating random\nuniform uint32 in the range [0, 2^24-1] and dividing by 2^24. This\nensures that the largest value is representable as a float32 less than\none.\nThis also changes the uniform double generation to use more bits of\nrandomness.", "body": "Generate random uniform floats in the range [0, 1) by generating random\r\nuniform uint32 in the range [0, 2^24-1] and dividing by 2^24. This\r\nensures that the largest value is representable as a float32 less than\r\none.\r\n\r\nThis also changes the uniform double generation to use more bits of\r\nrandomness."}